import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_capitals = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    state_capitals = state_capitals.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(state_capitals['state'], state_capitals['counts'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=state_capitals['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max number of state capitals: {:.2f}'.format(state_capitals['counts'].max()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the distance matrix
    coords = data[['lat', 'lon']].values
    dist_matrix = squareform(pdist(coords))

    # Create the heatmap
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10))
    heatmap = ax.imshow(dist_matrix, cmap='YlOrRd')

    # Add colorbar
    cbar = ax.figure.colorbar(heatmap, ax=ax)
    cbar.ax.set_ylabel('Distance (km)', rotation=-90, va="bottom")

    # Set title and axis labels
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance between state capitals?')
    ax.set_xticks(range(len(data)))
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['city'], rotation=90)
    ax.set_yticks(range(len(data)))
    ax.set_yticklabels(data['city'])

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_names = data['city'].tolist()
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='white', 
                min_font_size = 10).generate(' '.join(city_names))
    plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8), facecolor = None) 
    plt.imshow(wordcloud) 
    plt.axis("off") 
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 0) 
    plt.title('What is the most common city name for state capitals?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd

us_states = gpd.read_file('https://d2ad6b4ur7yvpq.cloudfront.net/naturalearth-3.3.0/ne_110m_admin_1_states_provinces_lakes.shp')
us_states = us_states[us_states['admin'] == 'United States of America']
us_states = us_states[['name', 'geometry']]
us_states = us_states.rename(columns={'name': 'state'})

data = pd.read_json('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vega/vega-datasets/master/data/us-state-capitals.json')

data = pd.merge(data, us_states, on='state')

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))

us_states.plot(ax=ax, color='white', edgecolor='black')

data.plot(ax=ax, markersize=50, color='red', marker='o')

plt.title('What is the distribution of state capitals by region?', wrap=True)

plt.show()
```
